7
(ADM) of one thousand five hundred (1,500) students or more,
7
8
appointed by the Governor, the President Pro Tempore of the Senate,
8
9
and the Speaker of the House of Representatives;
9
10
2. Three public school district administrators or athletic
10
11
directors employed by districts with an ADM of less than one
11
12
thousand five hundred (1,500) students, appointed by the Governor,
12
13
the President Pro Tempore of the Senate, and the Speaker of the
13
14
House of Representatives;
14
15
3. Three parents or legal guardians of students enrolled in
15
16
public school districts with an ADM of seven hundred fifty (750)
16
17
students or more, appointed by the Governor, the President Pro
17
18
Tempore of the Senate, and the Speaker of the House of
18
19
Representatives;
