C. 1. Initial appointments shall be made by August 1, 2026.
13
14
The Governor, the President Pro Tempore of the Senate, and the
14
15
Speaker of the House of Representatives shall each appoint one
15
16
member for three (3) years, one member for four (4) years, and one
16
17
member for five (5) years. Members shall serve until a successor is
17
18
appointed.
18
19
2. The Commission shall have an organizational meeting by
19
20
September 1, 2026, during which members shall elect from its
20
21
membership a chair and vice chair. The Commission shall elect from
21
22
its membership a chair and vice chair by November 30 every two (2)
22
23
years thereafter. No member shall serve more than two consecutive
23
24
terms as chair.
24
Req. No. 2707 Page 3

1
3. Members may be removed from the Commission by the appointing
1
2
authority for cause. Vacancies shall be filled by the appointing
2
3
authority for the unexpired term.
3
4
D. No member of the Senate or the House of Representatives may
4
5
be appointed to the Commission while serving as a member of the
5
6
Legislature or for two (2) years following the expiration of the
6
7
term of office.
7
8
E. The Commission shall meet once each month. Special meetings
8
9
may be called by the chair or by a majority of the members of the
9
10
Commission. Ten members of the Commission shall constitute a
10
11
quorum. No business may be transacted at any meeting unless a
11
12
quorum is present in person or through teleconferencing, and every
12
13
act of the Commission shall be approved by a majority of the
13
14
membership of the Commission. Each member of the Commission shall
14
15
receive necessary traveling expenses while in the performance of
15
16
duties as a member pursuant to the State Travel Reimbursement Act.
16
17
