A. The Oklahoma Athletics and Activities Commission created
1
2
pursuant to Section 1 of this act shall have supervision of the
2
3
secondary school activities in this state. Subject to limitations
3
4
otherwise provided by law, the Commission shall:
4
5
1. Promulgate rules pursuant to the Administrative Procedures
5
6
Act for the operation, supervision, and regulation of secondary
6
7
school activities. The rules shall, at a minimum, address
7
8
eligibility for student participation, usage of athletic facilities,
8
9
student recruitment, a code of conduct, and disciplinary procedures
9
10
for violations of the code of conduct;
10
11
2. Hire and fix the compensation and duties of an Executive
11
12
Director and other personnel required to carry out the duties of the
12
13
Commission;
13
14
3. Have the authority to enter into agreements with private
14
15
schools for their inclusion in secondary school activities
15
16
coordinated by the Commission;
16
17
4. Have the authority to cooperate with and enter into
17
18
agreements with national athletic associations as may be necessary
18
19
to promote, organize, or regulate secondary school activities;
19
20
5. Develop a plan to operate, supervise, and regulate secondary
20
21
school activities for all public and private schools in this state.
21
22
The plan shall be electronically submitted to the Governor, the
22
23
President Pro Tempore of the Senate, and the Speaker of the House of
23
24
Representatives by January 30, 2027;
